The Best New York Homeowners Insurance Companies

You may never want to think about the chance that you may experience damage to your home and need to file a homeowners insurance claim. Unfortunately, there are many things that your home may experience that would require filing a claim. But having one of the best New York home insurance companies can put your mind at ease that if something were to happen, it would be taken care of.

To help you be more confident in your homeowners insurance company, we have reviews and rankings for hundreds of home insurance companies so you can evaluate and compare the best New York homeowners insurance companies. In the table above, you can sort through every homeowners insurance company ranked on Clearsurance that sells in New York. Next to each insurer you’ll find the company’s rating, which is based exclusively on the reviews and ratings provided by customers. Note: Only those companies with at least 25 homeowners insurance reviews are eligible to appear in the best New York homeowners insurance rankings.

If you’re looking for additional information on one of the best homeowners insurance companies in New York, you can visit the company’s profile page where you’ll learn about the company, additional coverages and potential discounts offered. You can also read reviews to see what other policyholders have to say about the home insurance company.

On this page:

  • Cheapest homeowners insurance rates in New York for a $200K dwelling
  • Cheapest homeowners insurance rates in New York for a $400K dwelling
  • New York property crime statistics
  • New York disaster statistics

Who offers the best homeowners insurance rates in New York for a $200K home?

Of the five most popular home insurers in NY, State Farm offers the cheapest home insurance rates, on average, for a $200K New York home.

Compare the average homeowners insurance rates in New York for five different companies in the table below.

Company Average rates for $200K dwelling
Allstate Insurance $754
Chubb Group of Insurance Companies $1,196
NYCM Insurance (New York Central Mutual) $634
State Farm Insurance Company $525
Travelers Companies, Inc. $634

These rates are based on a $200,000 dwelling with the following coverage limits: $100,000 personal property, $20,000 loss of use, $20,000 other structures, $300,000 liability and $5,000 medical. The policy has a $1,000 deductible. The house used for the profile was constructed in 2004 and the individual had a good insurance score. The rates displayed should only be used for comparative purposes as individual rates in New York will differ. Rate data is provided by Quadrant Information Services.

Who offers the best homeowners insurance rates in New York for a $400K home?

State Farm, on average, offers the cheapest homeowners insurance rates in New York for a home worth about $400K out of the five largest companies in New York.

In the table below, you can see the average New York home insurance rates for a $400K home for five different home insurers.

Company Average rates for $400K dwelling
Allstate Insurance $1,413
Chubb Group of Insurance Companies $2,216
NYCM Insurance (New York Central Mutual) $1,111
State Farm Insurance Company $1,073
Travelers Companies, Inc. $1,109

These rates are based on a $400,000 dwelling with the following coverage limits: $200,000 personal property, $40,000 loss of use, $40,000 other structures, $300,000 liability and $5,000 medical. The policy has a $1,000 deductible. The house used for the profile was constructed in 2004 and the individual had a good insurance score. The rates displayed should only be used for comparative purposes as individual rates in New York will differ. Rate data is provided by Quadrant Information Services.

What do New York property crime statistics indicate?

Theft and vandalism or malicious mischief are among the 16 perils a standard homeowners insurance policy protects you from. So, how does crime in New York compare to other states around the country? The FBI published the following statistics on crime in New York for 2016:

  • Property crime - 305,181
  • Burglary - 39,821
  • Larceny theft - 250,968

When compared to the national average rate per 100,000 inhabitants, all three crime statistics for New York rank below the national average.

What do New York disaster statistics indicate?

Weather-related incidents are typically among the costliest homeowners insurance claims. FEMA has published statistics for each state since 1953. Data is updated through August 2018. Here’s a look at the New York federally declared disasters since 1953:

  • Severe storm - 27
  • Flood - 24
  • Snow - 20
  • Hurricane - 12
  • Fire - 2
  • Severe ice storm - 2
  • Earthquake - 1
  • Tornado - 1

How are homeowners insurance rates calculated in New York?

Ever wonder why you pay what you do for home insurance? Some things may be obvious, like the age of your home. But other factors that contribute to the price of homeowners insurance in New York may not be as obvious. Here’s a list of some of the things homeowners insurance companies consider when quoting you a rate:

  • The level of coverage required
  • The size of your mortgage
  • Your credit score
  • The square footage of your home
  • The geographic location of your home in New York
  • The condition of your home
  • The age of your home
  • The proximity of your home to a fire station
  • Your previous claims record
  • The amount of your deductible
  • Optional add-ons like umbrella insurance

Zillow estimates that homeowners can expect to pay approximately $35 each month for every $100,000 of your home's value.

The average cost of homeowners insurance in New York is cheaper than the national average cost that Americans pay for home insurance. Nearby states like Massachusetts and Connecticut pay more on average for the same amount of coverage. New York's lower home insurance premiums might be due to the fact that fewer homeowners are competing for policies.

When looking around for home insurance in New York, you'll come across several coverage options. To determine what type of home insurance coverage you need, you need to learn the most common causes of loss in the state. There are a few common causes of property losses that apply to most of New York: natural disasters, vandalism, burglary, and fire.

A standard policy in New York includes: dwelling coverage, liability coverage, personal property coverage, medical payments coverage, and additional living expenses. In order to tailor your homeowners policy to your needs, you might want to consider some optional coverage types. Extra coverage options such as: flood insurance, identity theft coverage, and personal property replacement cost can help you better protect your finances.

Talking to a licensed agent might help you figure out what coverages types are the most appropriate for your unique situation.
